  <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#Mixin">
    <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">A gufo:EndurantType that is both non-sortal and semi-rigid. As a semi-rigid type, it applies necessarily to some of its instances and contingently to some others. As a non-sortal, it captures properties shared by instances of different kinds.

For example, the type "FemaleAnimal" may be considered a gufo:Mixin as it applies necessarily to animals of certain species, e.g., lions and sharks, while it applies contingently to animals of other species such as clownfish and mushroom corals (which may change sex given certain conditions).</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#NonSortal"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#SemiRigidType"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Mixin</rdfs:label>
  </owl:Class>
