  <owl:DatatypeProperty rdf:about="http://ontology.amt.org/im#companyURL">
    <rdfs:label>company URL</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Relator-anchored: the company's primary web URL as captured by a specific relationship-instance (a lead-scan Registration's snapshot, or the Membership's snapshot at application time). Domain widened from im:Company to (im:Registration ∪ im:Membership) in v0.6.1 -- the URL is treated as a per-source snapshot rather than an identity-level fact, so different sources can record different URLs over time (rebrands, mergers) without conflict. The Company itself stays identity-only; to read the current URL for a Company, traverse ^im:mediatesMember/im:companyURL through its Membership.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI"/>
    <rdfs:domain>
      <owl:Class rdf:nodeID="n234f9bcb19864ff6b7dc566604c500d7b25">
        <owl:unionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
          <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.amt.org/im#Registration"/>
          <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.amt.org/im#Membership"/>
        </owl:unionOf>
      </owl:Class>
    </rdfs:domain>
  </owl:DatatypeProperty>
