  <gufo:Kind rdf:about="http://ontology.amt.org/im#AmtFacility">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:comment>Per-show record for an AMT-operated venue space that has a booth scanner but is not a commercial exhibitor -- e.g. AMT Member Lounge (S103), International Lounge (N226). Sibling Kind of im:ExhibitorRecord under im:Registration. Carries im:representsCompany (typically AMT itself), im:booth, im:registeredForShow, and is the target of im:leadOfExhibitor when a badge is scanned at an AMT facility. Does NOT carry im:hasProductCategory or im:servesIndustry.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:label>AMT Facility Record</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.amt.org/im#Registration"/>
  </gufo:Kind>
  <owl:DatatypeProperty rdf:about="http://ontology.amt.org/im#streetAddress">
    <rdfs:comment>Relator-anchored: address-line snapshot captured by a Registration (the visitor / exhibitor home address as of show registration) or Membership (the member company's HQ as of the membership application). Multi-valued. Never attached to im:Company or im:Person directly -- the value is a property of the relationship instance, not of the substantial entity. On VisitorRecord: PII (visitor home); stripped in pseudonymized fixtures. On Membership: street-level corporate HQ; still semi-PII (granular building address); stripped in fixtures.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:domain>
      <owl:Class rdf:nodeID="n234f9bcb19864ff6b7dc566604c500d7b7">
        <owl:unionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
          <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.amt.org/im#Registration"/>
          <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://ontology.amt.org/im#Membership"/>
        </owl:unionOf>
      </owl:Class>
    </rdfs:domain>
    <rdfs:label>street address</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string"/>
  </owl:DatatypeProperty>
  <owl:DatatypeProperty rdf:about="https://www.omg.org/spec/Commons/Designators/hasTextualName">
    <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="https://www.omg.org/spec/Commons/TextDatatype/hasTextValue"/>
    <cmns-av:adaptedFrom>ISO 639:2023 Code for individual languages and language groups, Second edition, 2023-11</cmns-av:adaptedFrom>
    <skos:definition>associates a name, reference name, or appellation with an individual concept</skos:definition>
    <skos:note>Note that the hasTextualName property defined herein has an implicit range of rdfs:Literal. This is purposeful, so that users can specify any element that has a name with or without a language tag without concern for conflicting datatypes (i.e., xsd:string vs. rdf:langString, which are logically disjoint).</skos:note>
    <rdfs:label>has textual name</rdfs:label>
  </owl:DatatypeProperty>
