  <owl:Class rdf:about="http://ontology.amt.org/im#Member">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#Role"/>
    <rdfs:label>AMT Member</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>A Company in its capacity as an AMT member. Anti-rigid Role: the same Company may cease to be a member without losing its Company identity. Distinct from im:Exhibitor (per-show role played for IMTS) -- Member is the org-level long-running role with AMT itself, scoped to the bylaw-defined member categories in mtrole_cs and self-declared market segment in ppl_cs. The role's data lives on im:Membership (the Relator that mediates Member and im:AMT); the Role itself is just the role-typing on the Company.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://ontology.amt.org/im#Company"/>
  </owl:Class>
  <owl:DatatypeProperty rdf:about="http://ontology.amt.org/im#badge">
    <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string"/>
    <rdfs:comment>Badge identifier. Stored as xsd:string because badge IDs are formally opaque -- the IMTS 2024 set happens to be all numeric, but new shows or future Maritz allocations may include alphanumeric prefixes, and visitor_raw treats them as strings throughout.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:label>badge</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://ontology.amt.org/im#VisitorRecord"/>
  </owl:DatatypeProperty>
