  <owl:Class rdf:about="https://www.omg.org/spec/Commons/Classifiers/Classifier">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.omg.org/spec/Commons/Classifiers/Aspect"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf>
      <owl:Restriction rdf:nodeID="Na1167b9ac5c24f1dad4f69ef3b5a922d">
        <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.omg.org/spec/Commons/Classifiers/ClassificationScheme"/>
        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://www.omg.org/spec/Commons/Designators/isDefinedIn"/>
      </owl:Restriction>
    </rdfs:subClassOf>
    <rdfs:subClassOf>
      <owl:Restriction rdf:nodeID="N0bc0e5c4ad0e4c2580fa1715dc9449ff">
        <owl:minCardinality rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#nonNegativeInteger">0</owl:minCardinality>
        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://www.omg.org/spec/Commons/Classifiers/classifies"/>
      </owl:Restriction>
    </rdfs:subClassOf>
    <skos:note>In ISO 1087, classifiers form categories of characteristics that serve as the criterion of subdivision when establishing concept systems.</skos:note>
    <skos:definition>standardized classification or delineation for something, per some scheme for such delineation, within a specified context</skos:definition>
    <skos:example>The classifier 'color' embraces characteristics being red, blue, green, etc. The classifier 'material' embraces characteristics made of wood, metal, etc.</skos:example>
    <rdfs:label>classifier</rdfs:label>
    <dcterms:source>ISO/IEC 11179-3 Information technology - Metadata registries (MDR) - Part 3: Registry metamodel and basic attributes, Third edition, 2013-02-15</dcterms:source>
  </owl:Class>
