  <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#standsInQualifiedRelationship">
    <rdfs:seeAlso rdf:resource="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#TemporaryRelationshipSituation"/>
    <rdfs:seeAlso rdf:resource="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#Relator"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">standsInQualifiedRelationship</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#standsIn"/>
    <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Identifies a gufo:TemporaryRelationshipSituation in which the endurant stands. The identified gufo:TemporaryRelationshipSituation is then used with the gufo:concernsRelatedEndurant and the gufo:concernsRelationshipType object properties to indicate the related element and the type of relationship that applies. This forms a pattern to represent that relationships that may change in different situations. For example, "heavierThan" may change when the objects involved gain or lose weight.

For material relations, prefer the use of gufo:Relator.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#TemporaryRelationshipSituation"/>
    <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#Endurant"/>
  </owl:ObjectProperty>
