  <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#Endurant">
    <owl:disjointUnionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
      <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#Aspect"/>
      <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#Object"/>
    </owl:disjointUnionOf>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Endurant</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">A gufo:ConcreteIndividual that endures in time and may change qualitatively while keeping its identity. 

Examples include: ordinary objects of everyday experience, such as a person, a house, and a car; reified relationships, such as a marriage, a rental contract, and a person's love for another; and existentially-dependent aspects of objects, such as a car's weight, a person's language skills, and a house's color. 

Also termed "continuant" in the philosophical literature.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#ConcreteIndividual"/>
  </owl:Class>
