  <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://ontology.amt.org/im#hasProductCategory">
    <rdfs:label>has product category</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://ontology.amt.org/im#Registration"/>
    <rdfs:comment>Self-classification of an exhibitor's offering against a product-category vocabulary. Domain im:Registration (v0.6.1) covers im:ExhibitorRecord and external exhibitor Kinds that sit under im:Registration (e.g. pc_jimtof_cs:Exhibitor). The per-Kind constraint that ONLY exhibitor-side sub-Kinds use this property is enforced by SHACL shapes in shapes/codeset-shapes.ttl, since a bare rdfs:domain declaration would either miss the JIMTOF external class (if narrowed to im:ExhibitorRecord) or force im.ttl to import the external codeset (a reverse dependency we forbid).</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:range rdf:resource="https://www.omg.org/spec/Commons/CodesAndCodeSets/CodeElement"/>
  </owl:ObjectProperty>
